## 11. TECH STACK RECOMMENDATIONS

| Layer | Recommended Tech | Why It Fits |
|-------|------------------|-------------|
| **Frontend** | **React** (Create‑React‑App) + **Tailwind CSS** | Component‑driven, fast development, responsive utilities; small bundle for low‑budget hosting. |
| **Backend** | **Node.js** with **Express** (or **NestJS** for structure) | Easy API integration, wide Indian developer community, good for rapid prototyping. |
| **CMS** | **Strapi** (headless) or **Sanity.io** (free tier) | Content editors can manage blogs, resources, multilingual content without code changes. |
| **Hosting** | **Vercel** (frontend) + **Render** or **Railway** (backend) – free tier sufficient initially; auto‑HTTPS, CDN. |
| **Database** | **PostgreSQL** (managed on Render) – relational for resource tagging, volunteer tracking. |
| **Analytics** | **Matomo** self‑hosted (privacy‑first) or **Google Analytics 4** with IP anonymisation (if consented). |
| **Security** | OWASP‑recommended headers (Helmet), rate‑limiting, CSRF tokens, HTTPS everywhere, **Helmet‑csp**. |
| **Scalability** | Serverless functions (Vercel) auto‑scale; static assets CDN. |
| **Low Budget** | All free‑tier services, open‑source libraries, community volunteers for dev ops. |
| **Student‑Led** | Use **GitHub Classroom** for collaborative development; CI via GitHub Actions (lint, accessibility tests). |

